{
  "texts": [
    "Let D i be a dialogue with utterances u i1, u i2,.... For a specific design component d ij in its final design (e.g., \"metal legs\"), we first retrieve the utterance u j that most closely matches with it (based on cosine similarity b/w RoBERTa embeddings (Liu et al., 2019)) -the conversational snippet associated with d ij should at least include u j.",
    "Next, we determine the contiguous utterances before and after this matched utterance that discuss the same higher-level design component (e.g., if d ij was \"metal legs\", the utterances may focus on discussion of the higher-level component \"legs\").",
    "We create a simple k-means clustering method to infer the higher-level component being discussed in utterances through their \"design clusters\".",
    "Then, we extract all contiguous utterances before and after u j with the same design clusters as u j.",
    "Using this method, we create a dataset of 454 conversational snippets, each paired with the discussed design component."
  ]
}